        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 3:50PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 349 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Fairview, or 9 miles northwest of Sweetwater, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Athens, Sweetwater, Madisonville, Englewood, Niota, Clear Water, and
Murray Store.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
